                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14794.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister to Mexico</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-07T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 7, 1915—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>618. Department just informed Carranza will not agree to neutralization Mexico
                    City or railway between Vera Cruz and Mexico City.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
